# RETICLE FastAPI — environment template.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in only what you need. Never commit the real .env.
#
# ── Secrets ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DB, SSO and secure-API values are NO LONGER kept here. They live in AWS
# Secrets Manager under RETICLE/* (managed by terraform/) and are loaded at
# startup by config.py using your default AWS credentials (`aws configure`).
#
# To run fully offline (no AWS, mock data) set:
# RETICLE_SKIP_AWS_SECRETS=1
#
# To read secrets by assuming the reader role instead of your own identity:
# RETICLE_SECRETS_ROLE_ARN=arn:aws:iam::<acct>:role/RETICLE-secrets-reader
#
# ── SSO (SPA model) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Auth is handled client-side by MSAL.js in the webapp (auth-code + PKCE, no
# client secret). This API only serves the PUBLIC config at GET /api/auth/config
# (client id + tenant, pulled from AWS). These knobs are optional:
#
# Webapp origin — used as the CORS origin and the default SSO redirect target:
FRONTEND_URL    = http://localhost:3001
# Override the SSO redirect URI if the app isn't served from FRONTEND_URL as-is:
# SSO_REDIRECT_URI = http://localhost:3001
# Extra CORS origins (comma-separated), in addition to FRONTEND_URL:
# CORS_ALLOW_ORIGINS =
#
# ── Optional local DB override (otherwise pulled from AWS) ────────────────────
# Leave AWS_DB_HOST blank to skip Postgres and run on mock/SQLite data.
# AWS_DB_HOST     = <rds-endpoint>.rds.amazonaws.com
# AWS_DB_PORT     = 5432
# AWS_DB_USER     = <db-user>
# AWS_DB_PASSWORD = <db-password>
# AWS_DB_NAME     = <db-name>
